uth in Europe using a large and original data set. It addresses some of the key questions around the issue including: How do young people cope with unemployment? Does unemployment lead to social exclusion of young people, implying a withdrawal from society, financial deprivation and social isolation? Drawing on a research sample of over 17000 young unemployed people in ten European countries, the book examines how different welfare strategies and labour market policies in different countries influence the risk of social exclusion among unemployed youth.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aMarginality, SocialzEurope. 0aUnemployed youthzEurope. 0aYouthxEmploymentzEurope. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Labor & Industrial Relations.2bisacsh1 aCarle, Jan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCaroleo, Floro Ernesto, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCartmel, Fred, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDietrich, Hans, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFurlong, Andy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGarrido, Alicia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHammer, Torild, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHammer, Torild, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHarsløf, Ivan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJulkunen, Ilse, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMalmberg-Heimonen, Ira, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPastore, Francesco, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRecotillet, Isabelle, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb